# Shannon for CLI — Environment Configuration
#
# The easy path: run `./shannon setup` — it auto-detects which agent CLI
# (Claude Code / Codex / Gemini) you have installed and authenticated, and
# writes the right .env for you. Nothing in this file needs to be edited by
# hand unless you want to use an API key or a custom provider.
#
# Prerequisites (one-time per agent you want to use):
#   Claude Code:  npm i -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code && claude
#   Codex:        npm i -g @openai/codex         && codex
#   Gemini:       npm i -g @google/gemini-cli    && gemini
#
# After `./shannon setup` succeeds, run:
#   ./shannon start -r /path/to/your/repo [-u https://your-app.com]

# =============================================================================
# AGENT CLI SELECTION
# =============================================================================
# Which coding-agent CLI Shannon should drive inside the worker container.
# `./shannon setup` writes this for you based on what's installed & logged in.
# Options: claude (default), codex, gemini
# SHANNON_AGENT_CLI=claude

# Per-agent model overrides — use these to pick a specific model or dodge a
# per-model rate limit. If unset, each agent CLI uses its own default.
#   List Gemini models: `gemini -m <name> -p ok` to test availability
#   List Codex models:  `codex --help`
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-pro
# CODEX_MODEL=gpt-5.2

# Upper bound on per-turn output tokens. 64000 is the recommended default.
CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_OUTPUT_TOKENS=64000

# =============================================================================
# ADVANCED: Manual credential overrides (only needed if you're NOT using
# a locally-logged-in agent CLI)
# =============================================================================
# Pick exactly ONE of the following if you want to skip the CLI-based flow.
# Anything set here takes precedence over the host's agent credentials.

# --- Anthropic API key (no subscription, pay-as-you-go) ---
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# --- OpenAI API key via router (for Codex or GPT models) ---
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-key
# ROUTER_DEFAULT=openai,gpt-5.2

# --- OpenRouter (for Gemini or other OSS models) ---
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-your-openrouter-key
# ROUTER_DEFAULT=openrouter,google/gemini-3-flash-preview

# --- AWS Bedrock ---
# CLAUDE_CODE_USE_BEDROCK=1
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# AWS_BEARER_TOKEN_BEDROCK=your-bearer-token
# ANTHROPIC_SMALL_MODEL=us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0
# ANTHROPIC_MEDIUM_MODEL=us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6
# ANTHROPIC_LARGE_MODEL=us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6

# --- Google Vertex AI ---
# CLAUDE_CODE_USE_VERTEX=1
# CLOUD_ML_REGION=us-east5
# ANTHROPIC_VERTEX_PROJECT_ID=your-gcp-project-id
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=./credentials/google-sa-key.json
# ANTHROPIC_SMALL_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5@20251001
# ANTHROPIC_MEDIUM_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# ANTHROPIC_LARGE_MODEL=claude-opus-4-6

# --- Custom Anthropic-compatible proxy ---
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://your-proxy.example.com
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=your-auth-token

# =============================================================================
# Model tier overrides (work across all providers)
# =============================================================================
# Override which model Shannon uses for each capability tier. Leave unset to
# use the defaults shown below.
# ANTHROPIC_SMALL_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001   # Summarization
# ANTHROPIC_MEDIUM_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6          # Analysis (default)
# ANTHROPIC_LARGE_MODEL=claude-opus-4-6             # Deep reasoning
